<h2>Who I Am & Why This Website Matters ğŸ‡µğŸ‡·</h2>
<p>
My name is <strong>Keishlyan Diaz Castro</strong>, and SazÃ³n Boricua was created out of
love for Puerto Rican culture and the traditions that live inside our kitchens.
Growing up, food was never just food â€” it was how family connected, how elders taught,
and how culture was passed down without ever needing a textbook.
</p>
<p>
This website exists because many traditional Puerto Rican recipes are shared verbally
and risk being lost over time. By documenting them in detail, I am helping preserve
culture, family history, and identity. SazÃ³n Boricua is meant for Puerto Rican families,
future generations, and anyone who wants to learn respectfully.
</p>
