<section id="recipes-en">
<h2>Traditional Recipes (English) ğŸ‡µğŸ‡·</h2>

<h3>Arroz con Gandules</h3>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> rice, gandules, sofrito, sazÃ³n, water.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong> Build flavor with sofrito, coat rice, simmer slowly, rest before serving.</p>

<h3>Pasteles</h3>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> green bananas, yautÃ­a, pork filling, banana leaves.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong> Prepare masa, add filling, wrap, boil, and rest.</p>

<h3>LechÃ³n Asado</h3>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> pork shoulder, garlic, adobo, citrus.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong> Marinate overnight, roast low and slow, crisp at the end.</p>

<h3>Coquito</h3>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> coconut milk, condensed milk, evaporated milk, rum.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong> Blend, chill overnight, shake before serving.</p>

<h3>Flan de Queso</h3>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> milks, cream cheese, eggs.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong> Blend, bake in water bath, chill, invert.</p>

<h3>Tembleque</h3>
<p><strong>Ingredients:</strong> coconut milk, sugar, cornstarch.</p>
<p><strong>Steps:</strong> Cook while stirring, chill, sprinkle cinnamon.</p>
</section>

